Bum Ghost: Greetings again, C.G. I was thinking the other day about my life, and I think you were right.
Bum Ghost: Still, I don't agree that happiness is everything, but it certainly doesn't help if I keep telling myself it sucked, no?
Bum Ghost: Besides, all of the ghosts here have a reason for being here, right?
Bum Ghost: They all have problems, and they're all dissatisfied in some way. Now, I maintain that my reasons are a bit more... dire than other reasons, but I suppose it's all about perspective.
Bum Ghost: What I'm trying to say is... thanks, Caf-Caf. Thanks for listening to me, and thanks for talking with me. You're a great guy, y'know that? A really helpful little soul.
Bum Ghost: What am I gonna do now?
Bum Ghost: Aren't you nosy, Cafe. Kidding, kidding.
Bum Ghost: I think... I want to stay here and watch what the ghosts do.
Bum Ghost: That tycoon monocle dude wants to make something, and he even got the column guy to help. I want to wander for a bit... until my metaphorical legs tire.
Bum Ghost: I think... I think I miss my parents. They're not gone yet... but one day they will come.
Bum Ghost: When they do... I wanna disappear with them. I don't know what comes next, but I want to confront whatever it is with them.
Bum Ghost: Thanks, Caf. I'll be seeing you.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
